                            <comment id="15881773" author="apachespark" created="Fri, 24 Feb 2017 01:55:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;markgrover&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/17047&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/17047&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16101096" author="diogo.mvieira" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2017 02:51:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you have plans to apply this fix in a Hadoop 2.5 compatible version of Spark?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Version 2.2 removed Hadoop 2.5 support&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16105427" author="mgrover" created="Fri, 28 Jul 2017 18:16:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wasn&apos;t planning on. One could argue the case that this could be backported to branch-2.1 given that it&apos;s a rather simple change. However, 2.2 brought in some changes that were long overdue - dropping support for Java 7, Hadoop 2.5 and even if we got this change backported, you won&apos;t be able to make use of goodness down the road you didn&apos;t upgrade to Hadoop 2.6, Java 8, etc. So, my recommendation here would be to brave the new world of hadoop 2.6.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16105514" author="diogo.mvieira" created="Fri, 28 Jul 2017 19:08:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, but it&apos;s a major security bug as described here. It should not be ported to 2.1.2?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16105952" author="diogo.mvieira" created="Sat, 29 Jul 2017 01:09:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did a merge request for this compatibility feature on version 2.1.2: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/18765&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/18765&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
